codex
I found a few small, bounded refactor opportunities that do not require changing tests: duplicate documentation, redundant path equality logic, unnecessary proactive suggestion work, an always-present empty permissions object, and duplicated denial parsing loops. I’m writing those into the required round-1 claims file with rejected candidates called out separately.
